{"key":"processedPost-12197532","value":{"id":12197532,"first":12147461,"last":12197645,"when":1268541692,"utime":"03/14/10 07:41 AM","content":"Let's all get along please.<br /><br />There is no 'time' to cool jars.&nbsp; You cool them until they're not hot, however long it takes.&nbsp; Being in a hurry and mushroom growing are mutually exclusive.&nbsp; <br /><br />Rapid cooling of jars via refrigerator or cold water, etc., is not advised.&nbsp; As substrates cool, they shrink.&nbsp; As they shrink, they draw in air from outside.&nbsp; If you cool them too fast, you can overwhelm the filter and allow contaminants to enter.<br />RR","title":"Re: Minimum Jar Cooling Time?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}